I was very excited about visiting this restaurant! It was the broadway avenue location in bushwick. I had driven past it a few times in the past week and said I was definitely coming back to try it. I enjoyed their fried shrimp basket but the catfish sandwich was a disappointment as seen in the pic below. There were 2 flat pieces of catfish and the lettuce & tomato were wilted and soggy. I was charged $9.99 for the catfish sandwich & cajun fries, which I was told by the cashier, came with a free soda of my choosing. I chose a pepsi, but alas as I unpack the bag, there's no soda. I'm not completely writing them off as they are fairly new, but I am guessing that the star of the show here will be their seafood boil bags.

I ordered from this restaurant 11/21/20. You can call and place your order over the phone and, they’ll call you when it’s ready for pick up. The woman that answered the phone was sooo sweet and listened to my order carefully. Everything was correct and sustainably packaged appropriately when I picked it up. The food was seasoned perfectly and delicious. Do yourself a favor and place an order. I guarantee that you will not be disappointed. I know that I’ll be a returning customer for sure.
